]]\n|align=left|27 September 2016\n|align=left|''Present''\n{{WDL|41|24|9|8|decimals=1}}\n|<ref name=\"Sam Allardyce: England manager leaves after one match in charge\"/><ref name=\"Managers: Gareth Southgate\">{{cite web |url=http://www.soccerbase.com/managers/manager.sd?manager_id=2034 |title=Managers: Gareth Southgate |website=Soccerbase |publisher=Centurycomm |accessdate=18 November 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n!colspan=3|Total\n{{WDLtot|225|96|55|74|decimals=1}}\n!\u2014\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n===Player===\n'''Crystal Palace'''\n*[[Football League First Division]]: [[1993\u201394 Football League First Division|1993\u201394]]\n\n'''Aston Villa'''\n*[[Football League Cup]]: [[1995\u201396 Football League Cup|1995\u201396]]\n\n'''Middlesbrough'''\n*Football League Cup: [[2003\u201304 Football League Cup|2003\u201304]]<ref name=\"Boro lift\">{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/league_cup/3507795.stm |title=Boro lift Carling Cup |work=BBC Sport |date=29 February 2004 |accessdate=18 August 2008}}</ref>\n*[[UEFA Cup]] runner-up: [[2005\u201306 UEFA Cup|2005\u201306]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Final - 10/05/2006 - 20:45CET (20:45 local time) - PSV Stadion - Eindhoven|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2005/matches/round=2214/match=84102/postmatch/lineups/index.html|website=uefa.com|accessdate=15 February 2016}}</ref>\n\n'''Individual'''\n*[[Premier League Player of the Month]]: [[1999\u20132000 FA Premier League#Monthly awards|January 2000]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/players/153/Gareth-Southgate/overview |title=Gareth Southgate: Overview |publisher=Premier League |accessdate=28 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Manager===\n'''England'''\n*[[UEFA Nations League]] third place: [[2019 UEFA Nations League Finals|2019]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48191915 |title=Nations League: England beat Switzerland 6-5 on penalties after 0-0 draw |work=BBC Sport |date=9 June 2019 |accessdate=9 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n'''England U21'''\n*[[Toulon Tournament]]: [[2016 Toulon Tournament|2016]]<ref name=Toulon>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefa.com/news/2016/may/29/france-toulon-final-report-280516 |title=England under-21s lift Toulon title after win over France |first=Nicholas |last=Veevers |publisher=The Football Association |date=29 May 2016 |accessdate=16 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n'''Individual'''\n*[[Premier League Manager of the Month]]: [[2008\u201309 Premier League#Monthly awards|August 2008]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/managers/3168/Gareth-Southgate/overview |title=Manager profile: Gareth Southgate |publisher=Premier League |accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref>\n*[[BBC Sports Personality of the Year Coach Award]]: 2018<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/sports-personality/46551056 |title=Sports Personality of the Year: Gareth Southgate named Coach of the Year |date=16 December 2018 |work=BBC Sport |accessdate=16 December 2018}}</ref>\n*[[FWA Tribute Award]]: 2019<ref>{{cite news |url=http://footballwriters.co.uk/editorial/gareth-southgate-honoured-by-the-fwa/ |title=Gareth Southgate honoured by the FWA |date=21 January 2019 |publisher=The FWA |accessdate=25 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Orders===\n*[[Officer of the Order of the British Empire]]: [[2019 New Year Honours|2019]]<ref>{{London Gazette |issue=62507 |supp=y |page=N14 |date=29 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n*[http://www.thefa.com/england/mens-seniors/squad/gareth-southgate Gareth Southgate profile] at the Football Association website\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n*{{soccerbase (manager)|id=2034|name=Gareth Southgate}}\n*{{NFT player|pid=2161}}\n*{{IMDb name|1351943|Gareth Southgate}}\n*[http://www.englandfootballonline.com/TeamPlyrsBios/PlayersS/BioSouthgateG.html Profile on englandfootballonline]\n\n{{Current managers of UEFA national teams}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = England squads\n| bg = white\n| fg = #CF081F\n| bordercolor = #0B0B3F\n